  <h2 id="overview">Extrusion Industry Hydraulic Oil Contamination</h2>

  <p>Dolphin Centrifuge, based in Warren, Michigan, supplies purpose-built disc stack centrifuge systems for this application at 24248 Gs. Hydraulic oil contamination in the extrusion industry is one of the most common &mdash; and most costly &mdash; operational problems. Extrusion presses operate under extreme hydraulic pressure, generating heat that accelerates oil degradation. Metal fines from wear, water ingress from cooler leaks, and carbon buildup from thermal cracking all conspire to destroy hydraulic components and trigger unplanned downtime.
  </p>

  <p>
    A centrifuge-based oil cleaning system is the ideal solution for extrusion press hydraulic oil. Unlike filters that clog and lose efficiency, a disc stack centrifuge provides <strong>continuous, automated purification</strong> &mdash; removing sub-micron particles, water, and sludge without consumable media.
  </p>

