  <!-- ── Preventative Maintenance ── -->
  <h2 id="preventative-maintenance">Preventative Maintenance Programs for Extrusion Presses</h2>

  <p>
    An effective hydraulic oil maintenance program for extrusion presses includes three key components:
  </p>

  <h3>1. Oil Cleanliness &mdash; Centrifuge Purification</h3>
  <p>
    Continuous centrifuge purification is the foundation of any extrusion press hydraulic maintenance program. A properly sized disc stack centrifuge operating in a kidney-loop configuration maintains hydraulic oil at ISO cleanliness levels far exceeding what filtration alone can achieve. The results are measurable:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>98% reduction</strong> in oil-related press downtime</li>
    <li><strong>99% reduction</strong> in hydraulic oil waste (oil life extended from months to years)</li>
    <li>Elimination of servo valve failures caused by contamination</li>
    <li>Lower pump replacement frequency</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2. Monthly Monitoring of Cleanliness Levels</h3>
  <p>
    Regular oil sampling and analysis (spectral analysis, particle counts, water content, TAN) provides a continuous record of hydraulic oil condition. Monthly monitoring allows maintenance teams to detect developing problems before they cause component failures. Trending analysis reveals whether the centrifuge system is maintaining target cleanliness levels and whether any new contamination sources have developed.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Regular Alignment of Pull-Back Rams</h3>
  <p>
    Misaligned pull-back rams create uneven loading on hydraulic cylinders, accelerating seal wear and generating metal particles that contaminate the hydraulic oil. Regular alignment checks and adjustments reduce the contamination load entering the hydraulic circuit and extend cylinder seal life. This mechanical maintenance, combined with centrifuge purification, addresses both the source and the effect of contamination.
  </p>

